60011.name: Prerequisite for Developing Neptune

60012.desc:
<color=#797979>Enough data must be gathered to ensure a smooth development process, and the most practical and effective data comes from live combat.</color>

 — Sortie and accumulate <color=#92fc63>1,000,000</color> EXP using Royal Navy Vanguard ships.
60012.name: Combat Data Collection Ⅰ

60013.desc:
<color=#797979>Investment in engineering is essential for materialization through development. If we can apply the results of basic research to cutting-edge technology, we could make significant developmental progress. </color>

 — Complete <color=#92fc63>5</color> Research Projects in the Tech Academy.
60013.name: Theoretical Engineering Research Ⅰ

60014.desc:
<color=#797979>Through a combination of the combat data and cutting-edge theoretical engineering, development has finally advanced to the drawing board stage. However, to work out the design's finer details, thorough comparisons between it and existing blueprints must first be made.</color>

 — Gather <color=#92fc63>10</color> T2 Cruiser Retrofit Blueprints (tapping "Submit" will use up these resources.)

60015.desc:
<color=#92fc63>Combat Data Collection Ⅰ must be completed first.</color>
The first draft of the design has been complete.<color=#797979>In order to verify to what extent the design's specs can be realized, more combat data must be gathered.</color>

 — Sortie and accumulate <color=#92fc63>2,000,000</color> EXP using Royal Navy Vanguard ships.
60015.name: Combat Data Collection Ⅱ

60016.desc:
<color=#92fc63>Theoretical Engineering Research Ⅰ must be completed first.</color>
<color=#797979>Next, the basic design must be revised, improved, and optimized. This is a perfect chance to implement the ideas we weren't able to during the initial stages.</color>

 — Complete <color=#92fc63>8</color> Research Projects in the Tech Academy.
60016.name: Theoretical Engineering Research Ⅱ

60017.desc:
<color=#797979>At long last, through a combination of theoretical engineering, combat data, a solid design, and revolutionary ideas, the Priority ship's design is approaching completion. We're hoping to fix some remaining problems to achieve the best performance possible.</color>
